# Husky-generated bootstrap dir (regenerated by `pnpm exec husky`, incl. `h`
# and the internal hook stubs). Must never be committed: a tracked copy
# lacking `h` breaks every fresh clone/worktree until someone manually runs
# `pnpm exec husky` (see #1649, #1920).
.husky/_/
# Accidental `gh`/tool state dirs created inside the repo when $HOME or
# $XDG_STATE_HOME is misconfigured (e.g. a sandboxed agent session);
# never legitimate repo content.
/.local/

vitest.config.*.timestamp*
